KAIZER Chiefs have joined the rest of the local football fraternity in paying their tributes to the late Cedric “Sugar Ray” Xulu. The soccer legend’s passing was confirmed by his former club AmaZulu on Monday. He was 81 years old. “The Chairman expresses his heartfelt condolences to the families and friends of the legendary Cedric 'Sugar Ray' Xulu, who passed away on Monday at the age of 81,” Chiefs wrote on social media. “The Chairman hails Sugar Ray for his immense contribution to the development of football and as one of the doyens of South African football history. Lala ngoxolo Gxabhashe.”  